recipies.title: Shakshuka
recipies.ingredients:
2 eggs
200g tomato juice
1 red bell pepper
120g russet potato
100g onion
recipies.instructions:
Precook the potatoes. Place them in the microwave or boil them.

Dice an onion and red bell pepper and add that to a sauté pan with a little olive oil over medium heat for about 5 minutes, or until the onions become translucent. Then add the garlic, tomato juice, potatoes and spices and stir for another minute, until the mixture is nice and fragrant.

Crack the eggs on top, cover and cook until desired firmness of yolk.
